newsitem.title: AUSTRALIA: RTRS-SFE active wheat futures track U.S. lower.
newsitem.headline: RTRS-SFE active wheat futures track U.S. lower.

text.p: Wheat futures in Australia tracked U.S. prices lower in continued light volume trading.
Trading was restricted to the nearby months, with most active January down A$4.00 to $157.50 a tonne.
Grains traders said the U.S. market was undermined by strong rumours that Egypt had rejected a cargoe of U.S. wheat.
"This spilled over to our market," one said.
With Janaury and March wheat settling below A$160.00 a tonne, traders said technical support, which has helped prop up prices recently, may be faltering, the trader said.
